# Testing

Both apps use **Jest**. Specs are colocated next to the source.

## Locations and naming

- `apps/api`: Jest `rootDir` is `src` and `testRegex` is `.*\.spec\.ts$` (see `apps/api/package.json`). Place specs at `apps/api/src/**/<name>.spec.ts`.
- `apps/web`: Jest runs from package root with `--passWithNoTests` today; colocate as `apps/web/src/**/<name>.test.ts(x)` or `<name>.spec.ts(x)`.
- Integration / e2e for api lives under `apps/api/test/` and runs via `pnpm --filter @gamevine/api test:e2e` using `supertest`.

One spec per source file, same basename. A source file without a corresponding spec is a coverage gap — the `test-runner` subagent will flag it.

## What to test

- **Pure functions**: exhaustive edge cases. Happy, empty, boundary, error.
- **Nest services**: prefer integration tests (real Drizzle against a test DB container) over deep mocking. Mock only at the network boundary.
- **Nest controllers**: `supertest` against a compiled `NestFactory.createTestingModule`. Test validation rejection (Zod) as much as happy paths.
- **Shared** (`packages/shared`): every exported function / schema has a spec. These are the contracts both apps depend on.
- **Web components**: test behaviour, not implementation. Prefer React Testing Library queries by role/text over test ids.

## Forbidden

- `.skip`, `.only`, `xit`, `xdescribe`, `fdescribe`, `fit` in committed code.
- `--passWithNoTests` is a bootstrap crutch. Once a package has any tests, this flag is tolerated but should be removed when all src files have coverage.
- Snapshot tests of entire React trees. Small, targeted snapshots only (and only when no better assertion exists).
- Mocking `@gamevine/shared`. It's a plain module; import it directly.
- Tests that hit the network. Use `nock`, MSW, or the supertest `Express` instance.

## Test data

- Shared fake factories go in `apps/<app>/test/factories/` (create if they don't exist). Don't inline ad-hoc fixtures in more than one spec.
- DB-touching tests get a fresh transaction per test and roll back (Nest + Drizzle pattern — write it once in a `TestDbModule` and reuse).

## Running

```bash
pnpm test                                    # everything via turbo
pnpm --filter @gamevine/api test             # api unit
pnpm --filter @gamevine/api test:e2e         # api e2e (needs Postgres)
pnpm --filter @gamevine/web test             # web unit
pnpm --filter @gamevine/api test:watch       # TDD loop
pnpm --filter @gamevine/api test:cov         # coverage report
```

Before claiming done, the full `pnpm test` must be green from root. See `.cursor/rules/definition-of-done.mdc`.
